hat you should use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_iconv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for streaming conversions."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Despite the fact that ","type":"text"},{"code":"bytesRead","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can return information about partial"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"characters, the g_convert_… functions are not generally suitable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for streaming. If the underlying converter maintains internal state,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then this won’t be preserved across successive calls to "},{"code":"g_convert()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_convert_with_iconv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_convert_with_fallback()"},{"type":"text","text":". (An example of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this is the GNU C converter for CP1255 which does not emit a base"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"character until it knows that the next character is not a mark that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"could combine with the base character.)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Characters which are valid in the input character set, but which have no","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"representation in the output character set will result in a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"illegalSequence","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" error. This is in contrast to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"iconv()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"specification, which leaves this behaviour implementation defined. Note that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this is the same error code as is returned for an invalid byte sequence in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the input character set. To get defined behaviour for conversion of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unrepresentable characters, use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_convert_with_fallback()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/convertWithIconv(str:len:converter:bytesRead:bytesWritten:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/convertwithiconv(str:len:converter:bytesread:byteswritten:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/convertWithIconv(str:len:converter:bytesRead:bytesWritten:)","title":"convertWithIconv(str:len:converter:bytesRead:bytesWritten:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Converts a string from one character set to another."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"convertWithIconv","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"str","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"len","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gssize","text":"gssize"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"converter"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GIConv","text":"GIConv"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"bytesRead"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gsize